During a visit to Nowhere Coffee Co. in Emmaus, Pennsylvania, President Biden was asked about Iran and the ongoing conflict with the Houthis. He stated that he has already delivered a message to Iran, warning them not to do anything. When asked if the US is in a de facto proxy war with Iran, he denied it. The President also expressed confidence in Secretary Austin but acknowledged that it was a lapse in judgment for him not to be informed earlier. Regarding the Houthis, he called them a terrorist group and said that the US will respond to their behavior along with its allies. When asked about the success of a recent strike, he mentioned that there were no civilian casualties. The President mentioned that he would speak further after visiting a fire station and offered to buy coffee for anyone present.